  "texts": [
    "However, the value of ϕ is not well-defined at the south pole of the (r, θ, t) sphere since both t → -∞ and r → +∞ there.",
    "This means that ϕ tends to a different value depending on the direction in which you approach the south pole.",
    "Nevertheless, since ϕ → ∞ at all other points on the boundary of AdS 3, it makes sense to use ϕ as a radial coordinate.",
    "We define the manifestly positive radial coordinate r = e ϕ = e t 1 + r 2, and we compactify the coordinates such that the spacetime looks like a sphere again.",
    "The ambiguity in the value of ϕ as we tended to the south pole of the (r, θ, t) sphere is now JHEP04(2024)048Significantly, we see that a theory of minimal tension strings on a background containing AdS 3 × S 3 (for the bosonization of the free fields) always comes with a global symmetry Φ → Φ + α, which we interpret as a shift in the radial coordinate."
